title: Fed cools interest rate hikes at June FOMC meeting
description:
At its June meeting, the Federal Open Market Committee unanimously decided to maintain the federal funds rate between 5% and 5.25%. This decision becomes effective June 15, and marks a pause in the Federal Reserve’s trend of rate hikes.
